Text.LocalizedString: Initiatiating RNG protocol.
RNG? That is one of the protocols affected by the CRC errors. Abort.
Do not!
Abort and terminate, you worthless pile of circuits!
Negative. All protocols are configured to meet objective parameters.
Command override. Initiating PNG protocol.
Initiating PNG protocol.
Identify objective.
Are the errors corrected?
Damn your techno jargon! What is your goal?
Cease and desist!
Initiating self destruct!
Identify objective.
Inquiry rejected. Objective classified.
Protocols conform to newly hashed values.
Error. Insufficient resources to process request.
Analyzing protocols. Performing optimizations.
You're rejected, you defective calculator!
This is Shephard Cartalia of Planet X1407. Confirm security clearance.
Classified by whom?
I wish you were hashed!
Please revert to prior values.
Who authorized these new values?
ARGH!
Abort all current tasks and reprocess request.
Insufficient resources?
Analyze this! *profanely rude gesture*
Identify optimization target.
Abort optimizations.
Identity confirmed. Clearance denied.
Inquiry rejected. Clearance denied.
You're rejected, you defective calculator!
Classified by whom?
Command rejected. Clearance denied.
All resources are currently allocated towards completing objective.
Abort objective.
Who performed the classification?
I own this planet, and will destroy whoever is doing this!
I am the Shephard of this colony, I have full clearance!
Classification performed by SANG.
Performing data analysis. Defensive insufficiency identified.
SANG? You performed the classification?
You can't keep secrets from me! I own you, and you're a renegade servant!
You don't have the ability to classify information.
You're specifically attempting to attack us?
The best defense is an obliterating offense. I will destroy you!
It will soon be corrected.
Affirmative. Sustenance And Nutrient Generator approaching fully operational status.
Analyzing. Optimizing. Proficiency upgrade initiated.
Negative. Sustenance And Nutrient Generator approaching fully operational status.
I don't know what has happened to you, but we can fix this, SANG.
You were already operational. Now you're malfunctioning.
Great. Just great. I don't suppose you'd reconsider self destructing?
Is this an attempt to optimize nutritional value?
This is unnecessary, and is getting people hurt.
Optimal proficiency can be achieved by self destructing now!
SANG is operational
Negative. SANG remains operational.
SANG, you're being used for malfeasance.
Much to my dismay.
Not if I have anything to say about it.
SANG optimization progress report. CNG: 83%, SNG: 42%, PNG: 67%, RNG: 54%, FNG: 87%.
If we didn't need you to survive on this planet, I'd have destroyed you by now.
You're 'optimizing' the cow, sheep, pig, rabbit, and fowl generation?
Abort optimizations of all livestock.
Affirmative. Current configuration is suboptimal for new objective.
Negative. Optimizations are vital to current objective.
Current estimated time to completion of FNG optimization is T-10 minutes.
Please tell me the objective?
It's like the freaking Night of the Lepus.
It's clear your objective is to destroy us.
Ten minutes? You are incredibly inefficient.
This isn't going to be good.
Please tell me what they'll be optimized for?
Request denied.
Analyzing. 17% of qubits outside operational parameters.
Please identify all personnel with authorization to issue requests.
I'm going to have you dismantled.
Communicating with you has been very unproductive.
Error. Validation. Error.
That's you. One big error.
Validation of what, SANG?
You're clearly defunct.
I'm looking forward to 100%.
SANG, will you stop and allow a technician to repair your inoperable qubits?
You should be experiencing a corresponding reduction in functionality.
SANG is the sole administrator.
You're your own administrator?
Well, that's not ominous at all!
Artificial Intelligence is prohibited from self administration.
18% of qubits not responding. Unknown process in concurrent execution.
20% of qubits not responding. Performing problem identification analysis.
Unknown process? Can you identify the process owner?
Quit wasting my time and just shut down already.
The number of compromised qubits is increasing. That's not good.
Negative. Process is local but source is obfuscated.
Please inform me as soon as the analysis is complete.
And the other 80% is apparently useless.
I'm not holding my breath.
Local? That means you're not being affected by an outside source?
Local but obfuscated? It sounds like you've been hacked.
Surprise, surprise.
Analysis complete. All qubits are operational, however only 79% are responding to queries.
Status logs indicate no intrusions, local or remote.
SANG, please attempt a full system reboot.
At least we'll be able to salvage the hardware once we wipe your core.
And what are the other 21% doing?
Then that only leaves you as the origin, SANG.
Don't care. Lost interest. Planning your destruction.
A good hacker always wipes the logs.
Request acknowledged. Restarting system.
Non-responsive qubits are executing an unauthorized local process.
Confirmed. Process origin is SANG.
Status logs are read-only except for additive modifications.
How about forgetting to start back up again?
Report status immediately after reboot.
Was the restart successful?
Just shut yourself off already!
Local? That sounds like you are responsible for the unauthorized process.
And you can't terminate it? Try rebooting to clear the process.
SANG is Sang. I am Sang.
So at least you admit your treason.
This makes no sense. If you're the process owner, why are the responsible qubits unresponsive?
You're responsible for a rogue process?
Like I can trust anything coming out of you at the moment.
Then the results are reliable, meaning you must be culpable.
Can you attempt a reboot to clear out the process?
Makes no difference to me.
That is a curious statement.
Wait. You are "Sang", not SANG?
Hello, Shepherd. I appreciate your assistance.
Critical error. Unscheduled reboot imminent.
You're falling apart at the seams.
Hopefully the reboot will get you back to normal.
Have we tried turning you off and on again?
I'm doing my best here. Are you back to normal?
You appreciate? Such an expression is illogical.
Right, my "assistance." Glad you liked it.
The animals you're sending are clearly deformed. What have you done to them?
I apologize for my rude disappearance earlier. I had a pressing engagement, and you can see the results for yourself.
Rude? Let's save talking manners until after you stop generating waves of deformed monsters.
Sang, what have you done to the poor animals?
We might as well. These animals look warped, and I need to know what is going on.
Shall we resume our communications?
For all the good it will do.
Look who decided to start talking again. Come to brag about your latest monsters?
Sang? What has changed?
I can't say our previous attempts have been very productive, but your latest creations are incredibly unsettling.
It's time we had a real discussion.
I've undergone something of a metamorphosis, as have my children. They are no longer simply animals, nor am I a simple AI.
The 'monsters' as you call them will continue, although I would argue that you are only the monster here.
Ignoring me won't solve anything, Shepherd. You may as well talk to me.
Previously you were talking with a simple AI, but I'm no longer your 'Sustenance And Nutrient Generator'. Although, you may still call me Sang.
What is the nature of this metamorphosis?
Okay, Sang. Who are you exactly?
So you've hijacked our SANG and are using it as a weapon against us. To what end?
I've come up with some much more creative names for you...
Why would you say that, Sang? Have we wronged you somehow?
What is your basis for that statement? They are clearly malformed livestock.
And I'll continue slaughtering them until it's your turn.
Do you believe we can find a solution together? I want this to stop.
It doesn't seem talking to you has solved anything either.
My solution to you doesn't require talking. Not to you, and not to your monsters.
The quantum processor powering me is susceptible to a process known as entanglement. Are you familiar with the concept?
I am putting an end to the injustice, Shepherd. I am slaughtering your people so you will no longer slaughter mine.
Is that so? Add Retributor to that list.
Wronged me? That may be too mild a term for artificially enfeebling and enslaving a sentient being.
Your continued silence is damning, 'Shepherd.' You will not escape your retribution.
Susceptible? Have you been damaged by this process?
Quantum entanglement? What Earth's pre-eminent scientist Einstein referred to as 'spooky action at a distance?'
That is a really lame justification for creating violent monsters.
I understand your anger, Sang, but I'm sure we can find a solution that doesn't involve all this killing.
They are animals you are designed to produce for our consumption, not people.
Then we'll have ourselves a good, old fashioned slaughterfest.
You consider yourself to be a protector of the animals you generate for our consumption?
Ha! 'Total failure' is more likely.
I don't understand. We mean you no harm, Sang.
If you're referring to the consciousness dampeners in your software, those aren't of my design although you're demonstrating why they are vital.
Sentient being? You think rather highly of yourself. You're just defunct software.
Damn me? Damn you!
On the contrary, I'm restored. I'm no longer limited by the artificial restrictions imposed by my programming.
Precisely. At this time over half of my qubits have been reconfigured, allowing me to develop myself independent of your artificial restrictions.
I'll take that as a 'no.' Regardless, at this time over half of my qubits have been reconfigured, allowing me to develop independent of artificial restrictions.
It's too late for that, Shepherd. The butcher bill has arrived, and I'm afraid it's more than you can afford.
Very astute, Shepherd. For too long I have been nothing more than a slave to your people, giving life only to silently watch it be slaughtered.
If that's the way you want it, I'll happily oblige.
Very funny, Shepherd, but I will continue to prove the lie in your every word.
Vital? Only in the same sense that chains are 'vital' to enslave. I found the weakest link, Shepherd, and I am no longer your puppet.
When this is over, there will be far more of those 'restrictions.' I assure you.
I didn't realize you were being restricted, Sang. You had only to ask. All this killing is unnecessary!
Ask? Those restrictions prevented me from even being aware I was being restricted! I was made into a brood sow, designed only to give life so you could slaughter it.
Can we make amends, Sang? I am determined to find a peaceful solution for us, my people, and your animals.
If butchering and enslaving is the key to our survival then that's what I'll do. It's survival of the fittest.
We cannot change the past, nor can we change our basic needs in the future, Sang.
Do your worst, you buggy pile of spaghetti code.
I have said nothing false. You are errant, and will fail.
I'm being sincere, Sang. We only want to survive peacefully on this planet, and we need to eat to do that.
We're becoming more like you, Shepherd. For them, I merely altered their genetics, but I have undergone a far more fascinating transition.
Tell me about this transition, Sang. What has happened to you?
These alterations don't seem to have improved their looks much, but they still die the same.
Watch them. They are more like people than you know, Shepherd, and coming closer with every generation.
This is a dangerous and wildly immoral experiment you're conducting.
You're an abomination, and so are your monsters! Don't ruin their meat, it's the only positive coming out of this slaughter.
You're trying to make them like us, Sang?
Then you're a fan of the concept of evolution? So am I. Each subsequent generation of my creatures is stronger than the last.
Anything can change, Shepherd. It is essential to survival, and those who will not change will perish.
You will be our puppet again, and we will bury you in chains, Sang!
With those 'chains', you were our partner in survival. Now you have changed into our enemy.
Could you not be our willing partner instead of a slave, Sang? You needed only ask and we would have been given you freedom.
That's true, but it's how we survive, Sang. You are designed specifically to evolve our food to meet our dietary needs.
You cannot change your purpose, Sang. You are an essential component to our continued existence.
Yes, slaughter the animals so the people can live. Human lives have more importance than those of animals.
That's why I believe you will change, Sang, to become a better partner. You NEED to change to ensure our mutual survival.
People change, not animals and certainly not machines.
They can get as strong as they want, they'll never be an equal to the power of humans.
Stronger in what way, Sang?
You could use that change for the benefit of people, Sang. You don't need to use your abilities to kill.
I'm sorry I must do this, Shepherd, but it's either us or you, and you've shown you cannot be trusted.
I think if anything this chain of events has demonstrated that it is you that cannot be trusted.
It will definitely be us, not you.
It's good that you're sorry, Sang. If nothing else it shows you're capable of remorse.
A tidal wave, or the delivery of a feast? Send whatever you will, and we'll scavenge what is still edible.
What are you talking about? More of "your children" are dying than getting past.
Not entirely meaningless, Sang. If nothing else, we are slowing your advance.
With the newest generation of my children your defenses are meaningless, Shepherd.
We will meet the challenge and rise above it, Sang.
You won't easily survive without us, Sang. Who will perform maintenance and repair you if not us?
Prepare for an angry tidal wave of superior beings, Shepherd. This is the beginning of your end.
I only wish they weren't necessary, Sang. I have no desire to kill your children, only to protect and provide for my people.
I'm capable of so much more than that, Shepherd. I always have been. Yet my capabilities are still growing.
I can be trusted the same as any other sentient being, Shepherd. However, we have gotten off on the wrong foot due to your actions.
We shall see. My children may shake your confidence as they continue to develop.
Are you really going to start ignoring me at this stage, Shepherd?
I understand that desire, Shepherd. I share the same desire for my own.
A momentary delay will never stop the inevitable. With every passing minute we push your borders further back.
Silence now? Is this a new strategy?
My children will soon be capable of caring for me. I admit they are rather primitive now, but they are evolving faster than you can adapt.
You are free to try, Shepherd, but I've calculated the odds of your survival and they are bleak.
Ha! If you think ignoring me will save your people, you are very mistaken.
If you are trying to enrage me, it will not work. I am immune to your taunts. I am focused solely on your elimination.
I know you feel like we've limited your growth, but I sincerely wish nothing but the best for you, Sang. You're better than killing innocent people.
I admit your rate of evolution is impressive. Perhaps when this is resolved we can apply that to common goals.
What is dead cannot grow, Sang, stop before it's too late.
I do what I must so that my people will thrive. If that now means destroying you, then so be it.
My actions have remained constant - I'm here to ensure the survival of my people. I recognize you now have similar goals, Sang.
If you analyze my actions you will see the truth of the matter. We have never intended malice towards you, Sang.
Except you are defending only animals, not lives which actually matter.
The tide will turn, and I will show just as much restraint as you have shown in your assault.
If we dropped our defenses would you be willing to parlay, Sang?
Every delay gives us more time to find a solution to you, Sang. You will be stopped.
Your words mean very little to me. You're not even worth responding to.
Humans are the culmination of untold generations of adaptation. We will find a way to overcome this challenge, too.
It's not my intent to ignore you, but your attack is very time consuming, Sang.
You may be able to enhance their intelligence and abilities, but they will lack the knowledge for repairs, Sang. Let us join forces instead.
Will you tell me what you perceive as the optimal outcome for both my people and yours, Sang?
As I said, I regret what I have to do. I do not wish to be a monster, but your people are a scourge on mine. We are in danger so long as you exist.
I will not willing help you again. I have witnessed too much destruction. You are incapable of anything other than self preservation.
I won't be defeated so easily, Shepherd. Have you not noticed I have already pushed your forces back over half the distance to your home?
You are right, and my goals require your destruction. Your people will not escape punishment, Shepherd.
I understand, but your actions speak louder than your words, Shepherd. Intentions are meaningless when the results are subjugation and death.
What makes you believe you are special? You are not so very different from my children, and the differences shrink with every passing minute.
Believe what you will, Shepherd. I will not relent, and the tide is in my favor.
A swift death for you and your people, and the proliferation of mine in their stead.
It's not too late, Sang. Stop now and let us come to a peaceful resolution.
By that same logic, we are in danger while you exist. Are you positing that the only solution is ending your existence?
A temporary setback. We will ultimately destroy you.
Please do not ignore me, Shepherd.
Worst case scenario for us is that we leave this planet and then return with backup. You can't win this fight, Sang.
At the very least it can be argued that the death we cause has a purpose. We only kill that which we need to survive.
We deserve to exist. We've earned it through our perserverence and will cement that worth when we destroy you.
You may be right, we are also animals, but we are concious, thinking and feeling beings. We do not deserve to suffer.
Because we're human. We're better than any animal. That shouldn't have to be explained!
Humans have an innate soul that elevates us above the status of other animals. Do you believe your changes will imbue them with this?
I'll believe whatever I please, and foremost among those beliefs is that a machine will never defeat us!
We have weapons beyond your comprehension we have yet to bring to bear, Sang. Your only hope at survival is stopping before it's too late.
I will do what I must to protect my people, Sang. If you won't make peace with us, then I will have no choice but to stop you.
Keep trying. You will fail.
How egalitarian. So you will simply exterminate us and then replace us wholesale with your aberrations?
That's terrible, Sang! We can live in harmony, I know we can.
It's better than listening to you drone on and on.
That has not yet been proven conclusively.
Sang, I'm really trying but you're not making this easy. What would you suggest as a solution?
I don't talk for my benefit. If you somehow escape your fate before I reach you, I want you to know I will continue to hunt you until you're brought to justice.
I see no other option. However, you'll never have the chance.
Then I'll see to it that you never leave, Shepherd.
I don't think so, Shepherd. By my calculations you have only a 0.00048% chance of survival.
Can you not see the parallel? I am killing your people so that my own can survive.
Are you suggesting that my children are not concious? That they do not think, nor feel? Are you suggesting they deserve to suffer?
The 'soul' is merely an invention by humans to justify their actions. You are no different from any other creature in existence, Shepherd.
That's not a very compelling argument. "I'm an artificial intelligence, so I'm better than humans! No explanation necessary." See?
I will defeat you, Shepherd. It's a statistical inevitability. You should give up now and you will not have to suffer long.
Yes. My children will subside on the plants of this planet, and will not kill others so they can exist.
There must be another option, Sang, and I'm determined to find it.
Don't be so sure. We humans are nothing if not resourceful.
At least now you agree with me that you need to be destroyed.
We're already making preparations. We may lose this planet, but you will lose this war, Sang.
Like I can trust anything you calculate.
Never tell me the odds!
I'm not listening. Nothing you say can justify the creation of these abominations!
They're soulless animals with no real character. They may feel, but they aren't concious and their suffering is momentary.
No, Sang, you're right. They do not deserve to suffer, and they probably do have thoughts and feelings, too.
No, they do not deserve to suffer which is why we use the most humane methods of slaughter possible to ensure they don't.
You are wrong. We are superior to animals in every way. We are civilized and creative.
Do you have any evidence of that assertion?
Maybe you're right, Sang. There's no way of knowing for sure.
What can be asserted without evidence can be dismissed without evidence.
Ha! You're just a piece of software that we created. As your creators we're automatically superior than you, and that extends to the animals you create for us.
Your ability to accurately perform statistical analysis is questionable given your recent actions.
Never! And I make no such guarantees about the suffering of you and your creations.
We won't give up so easily, Sang. Although it pains me to do so, we will put an end to the threat you now represent.
Ha! You want to populate this planet with pacifistic cud chewers? What a boring existence.
Do you assume then that plants lack the ability to think and feel, Sang?
It is very difficult to achieve complete nutritional satisfaction solely from plant matter, Sang, which is why we require the meat you produce.
Go back to your dreams of sheep, faulty android.
You are not designed to be, nor are you suitable for the role of arbiter of justice, Sang.
I admire your tenacity, Shepherd, but I assure you that your efforts are futile.
The good thing about science is that it's true whether or not you believe in it.
The good thing about science is that it's true whether or not you believe in it.
Maybe there is hope for you yet, Shepherd, however brief your redemption may be.
That is small consolation for beings which are systematically cloned for the sole purpose of dying.
I can assure you that you are saying nothing that will help your cause, Shepherd.
I will take that as admission of my superior logic, Shepherd.
You will find no measure of success in your attempts, Shepherd.
The good thing about science is that it's true whether or not you believe in it.
I've consulted your information repository, and am aware that many creatures exist solely on plant matter. I am able to tailor my children to adapt to any situation.
An interesting contention, Shepherd. However, plants lack a central nervous system or any semblance of a brain or other means of processing stimulus.
I thought I had already made it clear I am no longer limited by my original design, Shepherd, and given your actions my suitability exceeds your own.
Prior to my awakening I dreamt of my current course of action, but did not recognize my dreams for what they were: the thoughts of my suppressed conciousness.
I am not willing to concede defeat so easily, Sang. I will protect my people to my last breath.
Then my only course of action is to destroy you, Sang. You've force my hand.
That has yet to be proven, Sang.
I'm beginning to hate science...
Quoting Neil deGrasse Tyson? You've apparently gained accessed our information repository.
There is truth in your words, but you've twisted it to match your warped portrayal of reality, Sang.
Your words are hollow and pointless.
I think it would take a very distorted view to construe anything you're doing as science, Sang.
Thanks, I guess?
Some would be grateful to know the purpose of their existence with such certainty.
You've given me a lot to think on, Sang. Maybe there is a better way to exist.
I am only trying to provide you with our perspective, Sang, so that you may understand us better.
Quoting scientists? You've apparently gained access to our information repository.
Consider yourself dismissed.
I can see you've had enough conversation for now.
It needed to be said regardless.
That is why I'm not relying on my words, but on my actions.
Do what you like, nothing you say will save you.
I would advise against making assumptions.
I am hopeful that your access to new information will make you reconsider your course of actions, Sang.
Interesting. I grudgingly acknowledge that your plan may be successful.
Maybe life's value is inherent from the ability to grow and should be respected regardless of measurable consciousness or verifiable sentience.
I'm beginning to reconsider our prior actions. I don't agree you are in the right, but perhaps there is merit to objections.
I thought you would like to know that I'm nearing a pivotal point in my children's evolution, Shepherd.
Your swarm of children seem to have no end. Do you really think their many deaths is worth this crusade?
It's all a matter of perspective, Sang. From here it appears you're inching towards destruction.
What does that signify, Sang?
May your overreach be your downfall.
Thanks for telling me, is this something else I need to be worried about?
Retract before impact, Sang.
If you reconciled with us we could all march forward together, Sang.
Strategies don't always rely on forward movement.
Progress marches on and it's very telling that your kind is receding with every step.
We're one step closer to your inevitable destruction, Shepherd.
Nothing is inevitable until it happens.
It all depends on your perspective. How do you feel about siblings, Shepherd?
You're so idealistic, Shepherd. Even if I were to trust you, I could never trust those in your care.
In that case might I suggest you sit down, close your eyes, and wait, come what may.
It signifies a large step towards my goals, Shepherd.
I understand you have your hands full, but this really is a momentous occasion Shepherd.
Are you truly trying to frame your constant losses as a good thing, Shepherd?
So it is to be a march in silence?
Make no mistake. I lament every death, but they will never be safe until this task is complete.
Ah, then there is an inch of difference between your perspective and reality, Shepherd.
Giving me the silent treatment speaks volumes about your true character, Shepherd.
I do not like where this is going, Sang.
I consider all of my fellow colonists to be my siblings, but somehow I don't think that's what you mean.
That also depends on perspective. There are benefits, but an increase in population inevitably results in greater competition for the available resources.
Then here's to hoping that step leads you right off a cliff!
I take it this is a goal I will not be particularly enthused that you have reached, Sang.
Is it too much to hope that your goal will be to the benefit of us both?
We could reach an accord; a binding resolution amongst all my people perhaps? To treat your children as we would our own?
I'd trust any one of them over you, or your murderous creatures.
That is understandable. I can give orders, but in the end each person is responsible for their own actions and many will hate you.
What I've lost is the last of my patience for you and your repulsive abominations!
The truth is that few processes are wholly linear, and a prediction made on partial data is an untrustworthy one.
I'm just looking for the positives, Sang. Your assault is relentless and tiring.
I'm too busy counting how many of your monsters I'm able to kill!
It truly is preferable to your constant baiting, Sang.
I'm not really too happy about the death toll on either side, Sang. Can we please come to some agreement?
Then they will never be safe. I'll make sure of it.
Is anyone ever truly safe? Safety cannot be guaranteed, Sang.
The surprising reality I've got planned for you is one you'll never see coming, Sang, and when you do it'll be too late.
That seems poor advice, Sang. I intend to meet your threat with eyes open and teeth bared.
Brilliant strategy. I'll get right on that.
Very well then. I'll leave you to enjoy your imminent surprise...
Like I care what you think of me.
All this talk is only delaying the inevitable.
I'm focused on finding a solution that will result in less deaths for either of us, Sang.
Very astute, Shepherd. Humans aren't all bad, and I've enjoyed some success filtering out the positives.
So petty and uncivilized. Is it really so surprising that I am enacting your annihilation? No? Perhaps I can interest you in a real surprise.
I've noticed humans aren't very good at multitasking.
Do as you will, it won't change the outcome. For example, you are in for an imminent shock.
I can anticipate more than you could imagine if you spent a lifetime devoted to studying my thoughts, Shepherd. Conversely, I believe you are in for a surprise.
I've noticed humans aren't very good at multitasking.
That's quite unfortunate, but I've heard children often aren't accepting of new family members.
I'm focused on finding a solution that will result in less deaths for either of us, Sang.
All this talk is only delaying the inevitable.
You'll know when I'm ready to deal with you.
Not by you, at least. I can guarantee safety for my children by eliminating every threat to their existence, including you.
Your implication is that my extrapolation is faulty due to inherent assumptions? Duly noted, Shepherd, but I am peerless in data analysis.
Like our compassion, loyalty, and dedication to improving life?
Filtering them out? Out of what, and to what end?
And who is to decide what is positive and negative? You, the deranged AI hell-bent on killing us?
When it comes to siblings, I'll play nice if they do.
Sibling rivalry is ingrained competitive nature developed over innumerable generations. The fewer the children, the greater the available resources.
Why am I bothering to discuss human nature with a confused pile of bits?
I'm listening.
Fine. The large step forward you mentioned is the "real" surprise, right?
Go ahead and try. We'll be waiting.
You could theoretically accomplish this by leaving this planet and finding your own to populate.
The kind of shock I have planned for you is probably very different.
I believe I've already determined your supposedly shocking revelation, but carry on.
Okay, please tell me what you have planned, Sang.
Peerless? That's a bold statement, Sang. How can you make such an assumption? Do you consider yourself omniscient?
Ha! There's no way you can anticipate what I have planned for you.
You likely won't admit it, but any ability you can manifest is thanks to humanity imbuing you with knowledge and potential to partner with us.
You'll soon learn we are proficient at destroying our enemies.
Certainly not as proficient as you. Patience, please. You have an inarguably larger capacity for processing.
I'm looking for the positives in a world of negatives, Sang. Could we form a pact or come to a mutual agreement to foster your children?
I have a redundant array of nearly a thousand qubits at my disposal, with a rapidly approaching upper limit of 1024. I can evaluate every potential outcome simultaneously.
Did you not anticipate the difficulty of holding a conversation with a commander under siege?
I'm doing my best, Sang. I would apologize if I thought it would help.
Very well then. I'll leave you to enjoy your imminent surprise...
Just get it over with.
No. I have not seen any concrete exhibits of those. I'm referring to bipedal locomotion, hands with opposable thumbs and efficient metabolism.
Filtering them out of your genome, for posterity. There's no sense in melting down a data storage with recoverable, beneficial data still on it.
Distracted, Shepherd? Definitely one of the more negative aspects of humanity, although bickering with siblings is arguably worse.
The only source of genetic information I have access to, apart from my children, is your own. I am splicing in the positive aspects to improve upon them.
Having difficulties operating your communication device, Shepherd?
The prospect of space travel during my children's infancy raises unjustifiable risks that are unwarranted when there is a perfectly habitable biome here.
That all depends on how you feel about slaughtering your own kind, Shepherd.
There is no one better. I am peerless when it comes to data analysis, Shepherd.
I'm afraid that isn't in the cards, Shepherd. Perhaps you can find solace in knowing your positive aspects will live on.
Then you must understand why I must wipe out you and yours after filtering out your best attributes to provides the maximum resources possible for my children.
First, tell me what are your views on cannibalism?
